'''George Irvin Falgout''', born [[28 October]] [[1922]] in [[Raceland, Louisiana]], enlisted in the [[United States Naval Reserve]] [[19 February]] [[1942]]. He was killed in action in the [[Naval Battle of Guadalcanal]] [[12 November]] [[1942]], while serving in [[USS San Francisco (CA-38)|''San Francisco'']] (CA-38), heavily damaged in the battle. [[Seaman]] Second Class Falgout was posthumously awarded the [[Navy Cross]] for his great heroism and determination to defend his ship even at the cost of his life, when he remained at his gun, firing at a [[Japan]]ese aircraft until it crashed into his station.

In 1943, the [[destroyer escort]] [[USS Falgout (DE-324)|USS ''Falgout'']] (DE-324) was named in his honor.

